Canada Stocks Fluctuate as Mining Shares Drop, Bombardier Gains

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   A .   J o h n s o n
-- 
2011-03-02T15:57:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/bank-of-montreal-suncor-energy-canadian-equity-market-preview.html
Canadian stocks swung between gains
and losses as mining shares declined and  Bombardier Inc . gained.    Barrick Gold Corp ., the world’s largest producer, slumped
0.5 percent. Bombardier Inc. added 8 percent after NetJets Inc.,
the business-jet operator owned by Warren Buffett’s Berkshire
Hathaway Inc. ordered as many as 120 planes. Silver Wheaton
Corp. fell 0.8 percent.  The Standard & Poor’s/TSX Composite Index dropped 9.21
points, or 0.1 percent, to 14,113.64 at 10:55 a.m. in Toronto.  The Canadian benchmark equity index has gained 5.1 percent
since the beginning of the year through yesterday. Copper
futures have gained 1.1 percent for the same period and gold
futures added 0.7 percent. Oil has soared 9.6 percent since the
beginning of the year on concern political unrest in northern  Africa  and the Middle East will restrict supply.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Johnson in New York at 
